Class cabSquare

  • java.lang.Object
    • boardrelated.Square
      • boardrelated.buyableSquare
        • boardrelated.cabSquare
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Auctionable

    public class cabSquare
extends buyableSquare
    This class as the sub-type of buyableSquares allows us progress in a manner that the users can buy cab squares and in addition to that build some stands. It allows us to use a declared behavior of cab stands properties in many different ways such as the different rent policies under different conditions.
    Author:
    Cem Uyuk

      • arrival_proc

        public void arrival_proc(Player p,
                         Game g)
        Applies the arrival procedure of a cab square. If there are different number of cab squares owned by the same owner. Than the rent increases gradually. Such as, if there is a cab stand 60 for 1 cab square, 120 for 2, 240 for 3, 480 for 4. The rents gets half if there is no cab stand.
        Overrides:
        arrival_proc in class Square
        Parameters:
        p - The player who landed on the square
        g - The game that player and the square exist.
        See Also:
        Square.arrival_proc(backend.Player, backend.Game)
        Requires:
        A player to land on.
        Modifies:
        Increases the balance of the owner., Decreases the balance of the arriving player.
